# selection.py Split — Full Spec (SensorFlow)

> **Single handoff file, compact — this is a PURE MOVE.** No renames, no signature changes,
> no logic edits, no "while I'm here." One commit. Prep step for the crowding-distance +
> duplicate-feedback build, which lands INTO this module next.
> Names below are BEHAVIORAL descriptions, not a checklist to type — step 1 discovers the
> real names in runner.py; [MATCH, DON'T INVENT] throughout.

## PART I — DESIGN (brief)

**Goal:** isolate search strategy from orchestration. `sensorflow_v0/selection.py` receives,
moved verbatim, everything that answers two questions and nothing else:
1. **"Which archive entry becomes the parent?"** — the parent-selection function and its
   direct helpers (protection-window logic, frontier-extreme picking, best-on-a-metric
   lookup, target-metric choice).
2. **"Which operator runs this try?"** — the operator-choice function and its machinery
   (the registry table, eligibility helpers, the novelty decay-weight function, the repair
   gate's recency check if it's a standalone function; if inline, it moves with its owner).

**Constants rule (behavioral, not a name list):** a constant moves to selection.py iff it is
read ONLY by the functions above — operator weights, gates, decay parameters, protection
windows and their scaling factors. A constant read by anything else (metric policy,
diagnostics) stays in config.py and is imported. Step 1 produces the actual partition by
grepping consumers; ambiguous cases get flagged, not guessed.

**The one real design point — the shared RNG.** The moved functions draw from the shared
seeded RNG instance. If it currently lives in runner.py, selection.py cannot import it from
there (circular: runner imports selection). Resolution, locked: **the RNG instance moves to
config.py**; runner and selection both import it. This is the only permitted change beyond
file moves + import lines, and it must preserve single-instance semantics — one Random
object, same seed as today, no copies. (Draw order can only shift if module-level draws
exist — step 1 verifies there are none.)

**Out of scope:** any behavior change; frontier/dominance code (stays where it lives —
hypervolume.py imports it from there and must be unaffected); prompts; archive; reporting.

## PART II — RECIPE (one chunk)

### Step 1 — [VERIFY], no code
Report, quoting runner.py:
(a) the actual names + signatures of every function matching the two behavioral groups above,
    plus any helper called ONLY by them (belongs in the move) — flag anything ambiguous;
(b) the consumer-partition of candidate constants: for each, which functions read it —
    yielding the moves-vs-stays split per the constants rule;
(c) where the shared RNG instance is defined and every reference to it;
(d) confirmation there are no module-level RNG draws (draws only inside function bodies);
(e) what hypervolume.py imports and from where (must be untouched by this split).
**DONE-WHEN:** all five quoted. **STOP** if the RNG has consumers outside runner + the moved
functions, or module-level draws exist — report before moving anything.

### Step 2 — Move the RNG to config.py
Single instance, same seed (as a named constant if it isn't already). runner.py imports it
from config.
**DONE-WHEN:** a `--tries 3` run completes and its tries.csv operations column is
BYTE-IDENTICAL to a pre-change `--tries 3` run at the same seed and args — this proves
single-instance semantics survived.

### Step 3 — Create selection.py, move verbatim
Cut-paste the step-1(a) function set and step-1(b) "moves" constants. selection.py imports
only from config (RNG, shared constants); nothing from runner. Update runner.py imports.
**DONE-WHEN:** file loads; runner.py no longer defines any moved name (grep each: only
import-line hits); moved function bodies byte-identical to their pre-move text (diff them).

### Step 4 — Full verification
(a) no circular imports (grep selection.py for any runner import: zero);
(b) the same-seed `--tries 3` twin again — operations column and metrics byte-identical to
    pre-split;
(c) the hypervolume CLI still scores a historical run dir (its import path untouched);
(d) existing tests pass.
**DONE-WHEN:** all four green. Commit as one pure-move commit.

